    "description": "Tokyo Soir Co., Ltd. manufactures and sells women's formal wear and accessories in Japan. It operates through Formal Business and Lifestyle Business segments. The company offers black and colored formal wear under the Tokyo Soir, Lanvin Noir, Aquascutum, Pierre Cardin, Fleur Noir Soir Perle, Individual, Soir Perle, Essence Soir Perle, Claire Noir, Soir Benir, Soir Neue, Soir Dolce, Emotional Dresses, Rifane, Soir Lab, Aproberry, Demikitte, Hitoiro Soir, Form Forma, Traumerei, Yukiko Kimijima, Lifanne Liz, Jenny Elbe, A.V.V. Noir, and Soir Rêve brands; and accessories under the Petit Soir brand. It is also involved in the provision of rental services for dresses and accessories; and operation of a salon. In addition, the company retails products in the food and drink, kitchen and dining, living, fashion, and health and beauty categories under the kuros brand. It sells its products through department stores, mass retailers, shopping centers, brick-and-mortar stores, and online stores. Tokyo Soir Co., Ltd. was incorporated in 1949 and is headquartered in Chuo, Japan."
